<div id="review_3026591443" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3026591443" />
    <a title="Kylie D" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/80033559-kylie-d"><img alt="Kylie D" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1527289322p2/80033559.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3026591443?book_show_action=true">Oct 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kylie D" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kylie D" href="/user/show/80033559-kylie-d">Kylie D</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/44803146-knots-and-crosses">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80033559-kylie-d?shelf=mystery-crime">mystery-crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80033559-kylie-d?shelf=annual-challenges">annual-challenges</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80033559-kylie-d?shelf=monthly-challenges">monthly-challenges</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3026591443" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15865544222169992701">I first read this book many years ago, along with many others in the series, then lost touch with them, so I decided to revisit it from the start. In this novel we are introduced to the then DS Rebus, a flawed, very human character, who readers can instantly relate to, which is probably the main reason for the popularity of this series. Though not as polished as the later books in the series, it is still immensely readable, and gives us a great background to Rebus, and an insight into his person</span>
  <span id="freeText15865544222169992701" style="display:none">I first read this book many years ago, along with many others in the series, then lost touch with them, so I decided to revisit it from the start. In this novel we are introduced to the then DS Rebus, a flawed, very human character, who readers can instantly relate to, which is probably the main reason for the popularity of this series. Though not as polished as the later books in the series, it is still immensely readable, and gives us a great background to Rebus, and an insight into his personality. But be warned, this series will suck you in. Recommended for all lovers of crime and mysteries.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15865544222169992701" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


