<span id="freeTextContainer11235915003695893126">&quot;Knots and Crosses&quot; was first published in 1987 and is a crime novel. It is the first of the Inspector Rebus novels. It was written while Rankin was a postgraduate student at the University of Edinburgh.<br/><br/>This edition of the book was given out as part of a subscription, one of a series of &apos;Banned Books&apos; produced exclusively for the Independent newspaper and is book 20 in the series done to try and promote reading.</span>
  <span id="freeText11235915003695893126" style="display:none">"Knots and Crosses" was first published in 1987 and is a crime novel. It is the first of the Inspector Rebus novels. It was written while Rankin was a postgraduate student at the University of Edinburgh.<br /><br />This edition of the book was given out as part of a subscription, one of a series of 'Banned Books' produced exclusively for the Independent newspaper and is book 20 in the series done to try and promote reading.</span>
