<span id="freeTextContainer3526152952780366239">DNF @ 33%<br/><br/>Oftentimes I start a DNF review by saying something like it’s not the book it’s me, but in this case it’s very much this awful book. I’m 33% of the way through and there’s been zero progress on the crime that is supposedly the focus of the novel. Instead, we’ve been jumping between a few different POVs, several of which are very tangentially related to the main plot. It’s baffling to me that you would spend so much time on other characters when you’re trying to set up a main character f</span>
  <span id="freeText3526152952780366239" style="display:none">DNF @ 33%<br /><br />Oftentimes I start a DNF review by saying something like it’s not the book it’s me, but in this case it’s very much this awful book. I’m 33% of the way through and there’s been zero progress on the crime that is supposedly the focus of the novel. Instead, we’ve been jumping between a few different POVs, several of which are very tangentially related to the main plot. It’s baffling to me that you would spend so much time on other characters when you’re trying to set up a main character for a 23 book detective series. <br /><br />Sorry, but this book is absolute shit. </span>
